      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROMANTICISM (6) switched from a leading Victorian barn and has won both starts for the local Collings stable. He's been heavily bet and has had to do it the hard way in both. Third-up now and briefly freshened she can go on with the job. SAVAII (1) resumes for a top metro yard and won 3/3 in his initial preparation - and Collett sticks from those. Didn't get warm in her recent trial, but the blinkers are applied for the first time, suggesting intent. The betting will be key. LA MER BLEUE (7) switched from a Victorian yard and led and won a 58 at Nowra first-up on a heavy track. Draws to advantage and down in the weights will give plenty of cheek. CYCLONE RUPERT (2) this missed here third-up bouncing off a plain run. Has been kept on the fresh side and maps for a soft run. Has to be considered as well.",
